content.introtext:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;float: right;&quot; src=&quot;images/images/people/make_someones_monday.gif&quot; alt=&quot;Make Someone's Monday&quot; /&gt;In the week leading up to the &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.thanksgiving.org.au&quot;&gt;National Day of Thanksgiving&lt;/a&gt;, Robbo and Shelley gave Vision listeners an opportunity to say 'Thank You' to friends, family members, workmates, etc for something they had done. Some people were thanked for a one-off act, while others had faithfully served for many months or years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The response was overwhelming and many people said that it should be a regular feature on Vision. Well, we agree, so we've decided to make this a weekly segment whereby you tell us who you'd like to thank and what they've done and then we call them to thank them publicly on your behalf.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every Monday on &lt;em&gt;The Journey&lt;/em&gt; we start the week off by calling and thanking someone - we figure it will make their day (and week!) but we all feel good hearing about it too. It's a real win-win!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, let us know who you'd like to thank. Give us your name, the name and phone number of who you want to thank and what they've done when you call 1800 880 876 or &lt;a href=&quot;../index.php?option=com_form&amp;amp;form_id=14&amp;amp;Itemid=104&quot;&gt;CLICK HERE&lt;/a&gt; to send us the details via &lt;em&gt;The Journey's &lt;/em&gt;feedback form.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As you go through your day, take note of how much media is all around you... radio, TV, billboards, newspapers, junk mail, e-mails, Facebook, Twitter... It's everywhere...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And for good reason - it's an incredibly powerful tool... one that can be used for good or bad. Much of it focuses on things that really just don't matter... or half truths or opinion dressed up as truth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It just highlights how important &lt;em&gt;our&lt;/em&gt; media mission is... and every day we hear stories of how we're making a huge difference as a shining light of truth in this very mixed up media landscape!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But here's the crunch: &lt;strong&gt;Although the Gospel is free... getting it out comes at a cost.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

content.fulltext:
&lt;p&gt;Thankfully, thousands of Aussies have seen the potential in our media mission and have helped us come to where we are today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But our dream is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Christian Media for every Australian&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; so there is still much more to be done. That's why we'll be asking for your help with a tax deductible donation during Visionathon, in the last week of June.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It'll be an exciting week because powerful things happen when we work together! Think about how you'll respond... Together, let's &lt;strong&gt;RECLAIM THE FUTURE. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visionathon starts Monday June 21 - &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vision.org.au/vis10a_main.htm&quot;&gt;CLICK HERE&lt;/a&gt; for more details...&lt;/p&gt;

content.introtext:
&lt;p&gt;Three new communities have joined the Vision family in the last week! All of them are from Queensland, taking the state tally to 154. Here's some info about each of these towns:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Cleveland&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cleveland is a vibrant coastal village with a warm, friendly, cosmopolitan feel. There is an elegant marina, great places to eat and excellent facilities throughout the precinct. It is the commercial hub of the Redland Bay region, and the launch point to North Stradbroke Island. An important port for the Moreton Bay Settlement, Cleveland has many links to its colonial past preserved in a local Heritage Trail.&amp;nbsp; The Black Swamp Wetlands with its abundant bird and wildlife is a major attraction where it&amp;rsquo;s possible to watch thousands of flying foxes fly over each night at dusk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A short drive to Cleveland Point (the film site for the &lt;em&gt;Dawn Treader&lt;/em&gt; from the &lt;em&gt;Chronicles of&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;Narnia&lt;/em&gt;) &amp;nbsp;will reward you with great views of Moreton Bay. About 40000 people live in Cleveland and they can now enjoy Vision Radio on 87.6FM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Cardwell&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like Cleveland, Cardwell is transmitting on 87.6 FM. Situated halfway between Townsville and Cairns, it is the gateway to Hinchinbrook Island, an area of untamed wilderness, superb beaches, deserted islands, coral reefs and what is (so the locals say!) the best boating, fishing and wilderness locality along the North Queensland coast. Cardwell was settled in the late nineteenth century. In August 1884 there were some 25 houses and 50 people at Cardwell but the entrepeneur Dalrymple wrote that Cardwell should soon be converted from &amp;quot;a wild desolate and remote spot, into a flourishing seaport, within easy communication of the marts of the world&amp;quot; .... &amp;quot;filled with churches, public buildings and the warehouses of commerce, the black hulls of a merchant fleet in the harbour ...&amp;quot;Australia will hold nothing more beautiful than the city of Cardwell and its port.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, Cardwell has a population of approximately 1200 people and is the only town where the highway meets the sea north of Bowen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Vale View&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vale View is located just south of Toowoomba and is home to Federation Park. Country hospitality and old-fashioned charm meet in this tranquil setting of fields of golden grain and sunflowers.&amp;nbsp; 'Steele Rudd' spent much of his childhood on his family's small block at Emu Creek nearby. The radio series &lt;em&gt;Dad and Dave&lt;/em&gt; was based on his stories and helped turn them into an Australian cultural icon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On May 31, Vision came to Vale View. It covers the towns of Cambooya and Wyreema. Vision Vale View is our 154&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; Queensland station.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thanksgiving.org.au&quot; target=&quot;new&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.thanksgiving.org.au/userimages/NDOT_Logo_Date_10.jpg&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;350&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;cmbody&quot;&gt;This week on The Journey, Robbo and Shelley have been calling people on behalf of listeners to thank them for something they've done. Calls and e-mails have been flooding in with suggestions of people to call and some of the stories have been amazing!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Examples of those who have been thanked are staff at a local hospital that cared for a listener last week, a father who gave his daughter one of his kidneys when she suffered kidney failure and a chaplain at a local school who has been making a positive difference in the lives of the students.&lt;/p&gt;

content.fulltext:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have someone that you'd like to thank??&lt;/strong&gt; Fill in the form &lt;a href=&quot;../thejourney.htm&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; or call 1800 880 876 to give us the details. We'd like to know your name and the name and contact number of the person you'd like to thank - along with the reason you want to thank them...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is all part of the preparation for the National Day of Thanksgiving which is this Saturday (May 29). There are many events planned all over the country this weekend, designed to encourage people to thank God and each other for the good things that we sometimes take for granted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thanksgiving.org.au&quot; target=&quot;new&quot;&gt;Go to the National Day of Thanksgiving website&lt;/a&gt; to find out more about events that are planned in your area.&lt;/p&gt;
