&lt;p class=&quot;cmbody&quot;&gt;Two months ago a new program launched on Vision called &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;20Twenty.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; The UCB News team were promising to give a biblical perspective on life, culture &amp;amp; current events - and they haven't disappointed!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Already, there has been plenty of positive feedback from listeners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are some of the highlights since February 1st:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Catching up with &lt;i&gt;Leading the Way Ministries'&lt;/i&gt; Josh Youseff during his trip to Australia&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Talking to Winter Olympic Chaplain Matthew McBurney in Canada&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Finding out from Dr Carl Wieland about the Creation convention being run in response to the Atheist Convention&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;EMPART's Jossy Chacko filling us in on his mission's goal of 100,000 church plants in Asia before 2030&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Learning more about Arthur Blessitt's trip around the world carrying a 12 foot wooden cross&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Looking into the conflict in Nigeria with Barnabas Fund's Ian Wright&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;

content.fulltext:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team tell us that there's more good stuff coming up in the next few weeks - including catching up with MAF Pilot Ken Evers when he returns from his 55 day round the world flight to help combat malaria and reflecting on our great nation's history in the lead up to ANZAC day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as the special segments and guests, a number of regular features have commenced and you can expect to hear more health chats with nutritionist Aloysa Hourigan and pharmacist Dr Geraldine Moses, finance tips from Christian planner Stephen Poucher, the latest from the Middle East with Ron Ross PLUS perspectives from regulars like Bill Muehlenberg, Chuck Missler and Dave Miers in coming months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It really is a great mix of interviews, stories and perspectives you won't hear anywhere else! Twenty20 is heard every weekday @ 10am (Western) / Midday (eastern) on Vision. A 'Best of' highlights package also airs each weekend. &lt;a href=&quot;/downloadProgram.htm&quot;&gt;CLICK HERE&lt;/a&gt; to see the local airing times on our programme guide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

