&lt;p class=&quot;cmbody&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Thursday March 18 is Vision's &lt;i&gt;Day of Miracles!&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Millions around the world are blind as a result of cataracts, but by themselves are powerless to do anything about it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In partnership with CBM Australia (formerly Christian Blind Mission), and a number of other Christian radio stations across the country, we aimed to raise enough funds to perform 1,500 Miracles - in just one day - as a contribution toward CBM's overall target of 10,000 Miracles in 10 days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Day of Miracles was a HUGE success with the target exceeded! By early the following morning, the tally had grown to &lt;b&gt;1609 miracles&lt;/b&gt; - more than a third of these coming from Vision listeners!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Thanks for your generosity!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/cbm_dayofmiracles.htm&quot;&gt;CLICK HERE for more info, including videos, tally updates and contact details&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p class=cmbody&gt;UCB News was first launched on Vision Radio in April 2001. Over the years the news team has grown and the dream has always been to provide more news from a Biblical worldview.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Recently, an additional early morning bulletin was added, meaning that UCB News is now heard Monday to Friday from 5am - 8pm (EST). Then, earlier this year, with the addition of Amy de Graaf to the news team, &lt;i&gt;20Twenty&lt;/i&gt; was launched, providing a broader mix of news and current affairs every weekday.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, &lt;b&gt;UCB News is expanding again!&lt;/b&gt; From March 6, UCB News will be heard on Saturday mornings, with hourly bulletins from 6am - midday (EST).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is something that listeners have been asking for and we're glad to be able to add these additional bulletins to the weekend line-up on Vision!&lt;/p?

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;200&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://photos-a.ak.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ak-ash1/hs293.ash1/22062_311503093631_84943273631_3386914_4418687_n.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;cmbody&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;How can they believe in the one of whom they have not heard? &lt;i&gt;(Romans 10:14)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Attention all Melbournians!!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can now partner with Vision Radio to see Christ's message reach the people of your city. Host our Vision Radio Network Billboard at your church! Help us tell more people the good news that we are on air. Your help will see people reached through the gospel.&lt;/p&gt;

content.fulltext:
&lt;p&gt;If your church is looking for a way to extend its Christian ministry then hosting our vision trailer is a great way to start.  Not only does it encourage outreach in your community but it allows us at Vision Radio to partner with you in &lt;i&gt;Connecting Faith to Life&lt;/i&gt; and building a community of mature Christians.  We want to help YOU encourage the body of Christ and we hope to do that through providing your city with solid Christian radio and trustworthy biblical resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let us explain how you can partner with us to see lives transformed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vision Radio is only possible through the grace of God and from generous supporters like you.  If you're interested in displaying our Vision radio mobile billboard, here's what you need to do:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Check out the pictures of our trailer (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.facebook.com/album.php?aid=148469&amp;amp;id=84943273631&quot; target=&quot;new&quot;&gt;see more here&lt;/a&gt;). Our trailer dimensions for the face of the signs are 2.4 x 1.2m.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Talk to your church leader or business owner about how long you'd like to put our trailer in a clearly visible location (you can keep it for as little as two weeks or as long as you'd like - within reason).  NB: We tend to write up schedules so that our trailer can move from church to church with ease. We'd appreciate your help in keeping a schedule for our trailers visits.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Nominate some people who would be willing to pick up the trailer from a neighbouring church or possibly drop it off to another place when you are done.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Call us to discuss, time, location, length of hosting and away we go!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;It's that simple!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But our partnership doesn't end there; we can also provide you with stickers, banners, posters, pens, devotionals (and more!) to display in your church so that everyone can experience Vision Radio Network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Call us to organise hosting our mobile billboard today! If you have any questions or would like to speak to someone directly, please call and ask for Richelle on freecall 1800 00 777 0 or &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:marketing@ucb.com.au?subject=Melbourne mobile billboard enquiry (from Vision website)&quot;&gt;send her an e-mail.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.facebook.com/album.php?aid=148469&amp;amp;id=84943273631&quot; target=&quot;new&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;200&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://photos-c.ak.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ak-ash1/hs293.ash1/22062_311503108631_84943273631_3386917_5649719_n.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
CLICK HERE TO SEE MORE IMAGES&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

