content.introtext:
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Vision Nuriootpa 87.6 FM began transmitting on Friday 22 January. &amp;nbsp;The new station is the 45&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;in SA - welcome to the Vision family!&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img hspace=&quot;15&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://www.vision.org.au/images/haiti_earthquake.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;cmbody&quot;&gt;We've all been shocked as we watch the new reports of the 7.0 magnitude earthquake that hit the nation of Haiti earlier this week. While it's still far from clear, predictions are that the death toll will exceed 100,000. More than 3 million people have been directly affected by this natural disaster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;new&quot; href=&quot;http://news.google.com.au/news/search?aq=f&amp;amp;um=1&amp;amp;cf=all&amp;amp;ned=au&amp;amp;hl=en&amp;amp;q=haiti+earthquake&quot;&gt;CLICK HERE&lt;/a&gt; for the latest from Google News.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Being so far away, there can often be a feeling of hopelessness, that there is nothing we can do to help. But this isn't true! There are two significant ways that we can support the people of Haiti at this time.

content.fulltext:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first (and most important) thing is to &lt;b&gt;PRAY&lt;/b&gt;. James 5.16 says &amp;quot;The earnest prayer of a righteous person has great power and produces wonderful results.&amp;quot; (NLT) Pray for the rescue teams, aid workers, soldiers, those who are still trapped alive and for the Haitian people that they will be able to rebuild after this enormous tragedy...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The second way we can help is to &lt;b&gt;GIVE&lt;/b&gt;. There are many reputable Christian aid organisations already working in Haiti. By donating to their appeals, we can be confident that these funds will help where they are needed, paying for medical help, water, food, fuel, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;LINKS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many organisations that have appeals running. You can choose where to give - but the important thing is that we all respond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are a few that Vision endorses:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.compassion.com.au/cmspage.php?intid=343&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;200&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;padding-right: 25px;&quot; src=&quot;http://www.vision.org.au/images/Compassion_Web_Banner_02.gif&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.samaritanspurse.org.au&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://www.vision.org.au/images/SP_Haiti_relief.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cbm.org.au/Content.aspx?id=303&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;200&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;padding-left: 25px;&quot; src=&quot;http://www.vision.org.au/images/CBM_Haiti_relief.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

content.introtext:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;cmteaser&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;cmbody&quot;&gt;&lt;img hspace=&quot;15&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; src=&quot;http://www.familylifeaustralia.com/images/stories/radio_and_pods/EricandLori.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;For years, Vision has been bringing you practical help through &lt;i&gt;Focus on the Family&lt;/i&gt; each weekday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now we're pleased to launch a &lt;b&gt;brand new&lt;/b&gt; Aussie made program on the weekend to help with even more practical advice, inspiration and encouragement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It's called &lt;strong&gt;&lt;i&gt;Marriage &amp;amp; FamilyLife&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

content.fulltext:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hosted by Eric Skattebo, &amp;quot;Marriage &amp;amp; FamilyLife&amp;quot; covers a variety of topics - while clearly letting listeners know THE SOURCE of our strength and guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
