&lt;p&gt;The night will also feature special guest performing artist Steve Grace (pictured right), launching his Heritage Tour 2010.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About &lt;i&gt;The Word for Today&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It seems incredible that only fifteen years ago, &lt;i&gt;The Word for Today&lt;/i&gt; was launched with a readership of only a few thousand people. Today, over six million people in 25 nations around the world read it in 14 different languages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many Aussies report that &lt;i&gt;The Word for Today&lt;/i&gt; has challenged them to come back to God, opened their eyes in the first place to the truth of the Gospel or brought just the right guidance just when it was needed.  Well over 100,000 Aussies receive it as a print publication, as an email, on-air, on-line or in the youth version, word4U2day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One reader testifies:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&amp;quot;Praise God for &lt;i&gt;The Word for Today&lt;/i&gt;. It has helped me through many years of struggle and heartache... I have been so blessed and encouraged in my spiritual walk because of &lt;i&gt;The Word for Today&lt;/i&gt;. Keep up the good work of encouraging the community in Christ Jesus.&amp;quot;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
